*Question to be answered with the PhD Supervisors :

**For the applicant, how did you prepare your research project with your supervisors (200words): 

	After investigations in order to find a team with whom I was able to carry out a thesis project, we started looking for common interests. After several discussions on what Samuel Bottani and Catherine Villard were working on we manage to ascertain specific scope that on one hand needed to be answered and on the other hand could be answered with the ressources we have. 
	The way we proceed afterwards so as to find the right words to narrow down the central point of the project was the following. Samuel and Catherine provided the scientific expertise and a preliminary draft to help me with things I did not master at that time. After learning a lot with various references they would gave me, I was able see and develop my project the way I though best. 
	With the lucid questioning of Catherine and Samuel on what I wrote, we ended up with the final project. In the end the research proposal was established by all three us with my personal questioning and their scientific advices.  

**Summary of primary supervisor’s work : (max500words) 

My group with Pascal Monceau and Stéphane Métens at the MSC lab works on theoretical approaches of information processing, auto-organization and network structure in dissociated neuronal cultures. With specific skills on simulations, biophysics modeling and non dynamical systems, we aim at a further the understanding of the observed spontaneous bursting and avalanche activity on planar cultures and how synaptic plasticity plays at the population scale. 

